        public CandidateFluxDomain(java.lang.String domainName,
                   java.util.Date firstSeen,
                   java.util.Date lastSeen,
                   java.util.Date reportedAt,
                   long numMessages,
                   long numQueries,
                   long minTTL,
                   long maxTTL,
                   double avgTTL,
                   java.lang.Double lastGrowthRatioSingleEntry,
                   java.util.Set<java.net.InetAddress> ips,
                   java.util.Set<java.net.InetAddress> lastGrowthEntriesIPs,
                   long lastGrowthEntriesQueries)
        Instantiates a new candidate flux domain.
        Parameters:
        domainName - the domain name
        firstSeen - the date first seen in the input data
        lastSeen - the date last seen in the input data
        reportedAt - the date when the domain was reported in the input data
        numMessages - the num messages
        numQueries - the number of dns queries for the domain
        minTTL - the min ttl of a dns query to the domain
        maxTTL - the max ttl of a dns query to the domain
        avgTTL - the avg ttl of a dns query to the domain
        lastGrowthRatioSingleEntry - the last growth ratio single entry feature of the domain
        ips - the list of IP addresses to which the domain name resolved in the input data
        lastGrowthEntriesIPs - the last growth entries IPs feature of the domain
        lastGrowthEntriesQueries - the last growth entries queries feature of the domain
